                  <paragraph>1.  Clean the wound with mild soap and water.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>2.  Apply a topical antibiotic ointment, such as Bacitracin at least twice</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>daily to the wound with a cotton tipped applicator.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>3.  Keep a non-stick bandage or a Band-Aid over the wound.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>4.  Try not to let the wound dry out (form a scab) because that can</paragraph>
